  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. The simulation model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two independent laboratories under ASTM F1717 loading conditions. All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed; one factor (Test conditions) falls below the required level due to evaluation at a single load condition. The intended use is pre-market regulatory submission support for a Class II spinal fixation device, and the quantities of interest are construct stiffness and peak bending moment at failure. Credibility requirements are defined in the bound requirement document (see bindsRequirement). The model risk level is 3 (moderate), and the assurance level target is Medium per the risk-informed framework.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/req/f1717-compression-bending-credibility-req-v2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/claim/fea-f1717-noncannulated-compression-bending",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/model/fea-pedicle-screw-ensemble-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
